<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Corrupt2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Corrupt,</orth> adj. vitiated, depraved, perverted: <cit><quote>eyes c. by over-partial looks,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 137.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 137, 5</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>c. and tainted in desire,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 94</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the c. deputy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.265" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 265</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in law, what plea so tainted and c.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 3.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 2, 75</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.320" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 320</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 4, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 116</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.133" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 133</bibl>. Compar. <cit><quote>--er,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 2.2.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 2, 108</bibl></cit>.
